e world\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 440}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That she was prodigious, medaling at the biggest, toughest races before she could legally order an alcoholic drink, only made all she accomplished seem easy, predestined.\", \"from\": 443, \"to\": 613, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the biggest, toughest races\", \"from\": 480, \"to\": 507}, {\"ngram\": \"an alcoholic drink\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 557}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From her hometown of Trenton, N.J., to a worldwide stage in Tokyo, Mu set a slew of NCAA records and, in 2021,snagged a pair of Olympic golds, in the 800 meters and 4x400-meter relay.\", \"from\": 614, \"to\": 797, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 635, \"end\": 642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trenton\", \"score\": 0.8894944214207702, \"rank\": 0.1242341446081344, \"text\": \"Trenton\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trenton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trenton\"}, {\"begin\": 674, \"end\": 679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9697248958409214, \"rank\": 0.031220297966924618, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 681, \"end\": 683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9999999994151949, \"rank\": 5.844886024119947e-10, \"text\": \"Mu\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Minnesota\"}, {\"begin\": 698, \"end\": 702, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.939813045222535e-16, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia